          exercise: "Practice the 30-Second Transition today! Every time you finish one activity and move to another — finishing homework and going to dinner, finishing dinner and starting free time — pause for 30 seconds. Take three slow deep breaths, notice how your body feels, and say to yourself: Now I am going to do [next activity] with full attention. Do this at least five times today and notice: did you reach for your phone less during transitions? Did the next activity feel calmer? Write about your experience in your journal tonight.",
