          narration: "Have you ever been so focused on something that you completely lost track of time? Maybe you were drawing, building something, writing a story, or solving a tricky puzzle, and when you looked up, an hour had magically passed. That is deep work! It is when you give something your complete, total, undivided attention and your brain works at its absolute best. The opposite of deep work is shallow work — things like scrolling, texting, or doing easy tasks that do not need much thinking. Here is the amazing thing: as more people get addicted to their screens, fewer people can do deep work. That means if you learn how to do it, you will have a superpower that most people have lost. How cool is that?",
          exercise: "Make a Deep Work vs Shallow Work list! Draw a line down the middle of a piece of paper. On the left, write Deep Work and list activities that require your full brainpower — things like writing a story, learning a new skill, studying for a test, creating art, or practicing an instrument. On the right, write Shallow Work and list activities that do not need deep thinking — like replying to messages, scrolling social media, or sorting stuff. Now circle the deep work activities you care about most. These are where deep work will make the biggest difference for you!",
