          exercise: "Pick one skill or subject you really want to get better at. It could be anything — drawing, math, writing, playing an instrument, a sport, coding, or anything else. Write a paragraph about why it matters to you and how getting better at it would make you feel. Then try doing that activity for 20 minutes with absolutely zero distractions — no phone, no music with lyrics, no interruptions. Afterward, write about the experience. Did you notice a difference in quality? Did you get more done than usual? How did it feel?",
