          exercise: "Practice the Later List technique during your next deep work session! Keep a small notepad or piece of paper next to you labeled Later List. Every time a thought, urge, or distraction pops into your mind during your session — like wanting to check your phone, remembering something you need to do, or wondering about something random — write it down quickly without stopping your work. After your session, count how many items are on your Later List and take care of any that still matter. This shows you how many interruptions your brain creates — and how you can handle them all!",
